To do proxy IP set please follow below setps.
** to check the any existing proxy address
# echo $http_proxy
# echo $https_proxy

if no proxy address is set then use below command.

export https_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"
export http_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"
export ftp_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"

to make it parmanent 
# vi /etc/environment
https_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"
http_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"
ftp_proxy="http://10.251.xx.xx:8080"

to check the set proxy 
# echo $http_proxy
# echo $https_proxy

Configuring proxy for processes with SHELL

echo "export https_proxy=http://10.251.xx.xx:8080/" > /etc/profile.d/https_proxy.sh
echo "export http_proxy=http://10.251.xx.xx:8080/" > /etc/profile.d/http_proxy.sh

#for RHEL 9 & 10....
cat <<EOF > /etc/profile.d/proxy.sh
export http_proxy=http://172.18.200.5:8090
export https_proxy=http://172.18.200.5:8090
export HTTP_PROXY=http://172.18.200.5:8090
export HTTPS_PROXY=http://172.18.200.5:8090
EOF

reload the session
source /etc/profile.d/proxy.sh
